pulses.name: Iran APT Groups Exploit Papercut Vulnerability
pulses.description: In an update to our intelligence report published on 28 April 2023, titled PaperCut Exploitation Leads to Truebot and Cryptomining, VulnCheck published on 04 May 2023 a proof-of-concept exploit that bypasses all known published detections. Additionally, Microsoft posted a Twitter thread on 05 May 2023 that they observed Iranian state-sponsored threat actors, Mint Sandstorm and Mango Sandstorm, exploiting the unpatched CVE-2023-27350 in the Papercut print management software. Mint Sandstorm and Mango Sandstorm quickly adapted publicly available proof-of-concept exploits in their operation. According to Microsoft, Mint Sandstorm's exploitation of Papercut was opportunistic, affecting organizations globally, while Mango Sandstorm's exploitation activity remains low.

pulses.name: URGENT | PaperCut MF/NG vulnerability bulletin (March 2023)
pulses.description:
We have received two vulnerability reports from a 3rd party cyber security company (Trend Micro), for high/critical severity security issues in PaperCut MF/NG. We have evidence to suggest that unpatched servers are being exploited in the wild.

Remote Code Execution vulnerability (CVE-2023–27350 / ZDI-CAN-18987 / ZDI-23–233)
User account data vulnerability (CVE-2023–27351 / ZDI-CAN-19226 / ZDI-23–232)

https://www.papercut.com/kb/Main/PO-1216-and-PO-1219#faqs
